In [4]:
def heatmap_comparison(net_5,net_50, plot_name):
    dates = pd.to_datetime(['2008-03-01','2008-06-01','2008-09-01','2008-12-01','2009-03-01','2009-06-01','2009-9-01','2009-12-01'])
    fig, axs = plt.subplots(8, 2, figsize = (25, 85))
    for i,d in enumerate(dates):
        adj_5 = net_5.xs(d, level=1, drop_level=True).round(1)
        adj_50 = net_50.xs(d, level=1, drop_level=True).round(1)

        minn, maxx = min(adj_5.min().min(),adj_50.min().min()), max(adj_5.max().max(),adj_50.max().max())
        sns.heatmap(adj_5, annot=True, center=0, cmap = sns.color_palette("coolwarm", 7),ax = axs[i, 0],vmin = minn ,vmax= maxx )
        sns.heatmap(adj_50, annot=True, center=0, cmap = sns.color_palette("coolwarm", 7),ax = axs[i, 1],vmin = minn ,vmax= maxx )

        axs[i,0].set_title("5th Quantile on {}".format(d.strftime("%b %Y")))
        axs[i,1].set_title("50th Quantile on {}".format(d.strftime("%b %Y")))
    plt.tight_layout(pad=3.0)
    plt.savefig('graphs/{}_Network_Heatmap.png'.format(plot_name))

def load_data(path):
    data = pd.read_csv(path, index_col=0)
    data.index = pd.to_datetime(data.index)
    return data

In [13]:
mean_pw_edge_list_5 = net_5.abs().groupby('country').mean().reset_index().melt(id_vars = ['country'],  var_name = 'source', value_name = 'weight')
mean_pw_edge_list_50 = net_50.abs().groupby('country').mean().reset_index().melt(id_vars = ['country'],  var_name = 'source', value_name = 'weight')

mean_pw_network_5 = nx.from_pandas_edgelist(mean_pw_edge_list_5, source =  'source', target = 'country', edge_attr = ['weight'], create_using = nx.DiGraph)
mean_pw_network_50 = nx.from_pandas_edgelist(mean_pw_edge_list_50, source =  'source', target = 'country', edge_attr = ['weight'], create_using = nx.DiGraph)

fig, axs = plt.subplots(1,2, figsize = (25,10))

weights_5, weights_50 = nx.get_edge_attributes(mean_pw_network_5,'weight').values(), nx.get_edge_attributes(mean_pw_network_50,'weight').values()
minn, maxx =  min(min(weights_5),min(weights_50)), max(max(weights_5),max(weights_50))
sum_5, sum_50 = mean_pw_edge_list_5['weight'].sum(), mean_pw_edge_list_50['weight'].sum()

nx.draw_networkx(mean_pw_network_5, pos=nx.shell_layout(mean_pw_network_5), ax = axs[0], node_color = '#000000',font_color = '#ffffff', node_size = 800, style = 'dashdot', arrowsize=20,edge_color = weights_5,edge_cmap=plt.cm.Reds, edge_vmin = minn, edge_vmax=maxx)
nx.draw_networkx(mean_pw_network_50, pos=nx.shell_layout(mean_pw_network_50), ax = axs[1], node_color = '#000000',font_color = '#ffffff', node_size = 800, style = 'dashdot', arrowsize=20,edge_color = weights_50,edge_cmap=plt.cm.Reds, edge_vmin = minn, edge_vmax=maxx)

axs[0].text(0.5, 0, "Sum of mean pairwise connectedness: "+str(round(sum_5,2)), horizontalalignment='center', verticalalignment='center', transform=axs[0].transAxes)
axs[1].text(0.5, 0, "Sum of mean pairwise connectedness: "+str(round(sum_50,2)), horizontalalignment='center', verticalalignment='center', transform=axs[1].transAxes)

axs[0].axis('off')
axs[1].axis('off')

axs[0].set_title('Mean over  time of Pairwise directional Connectedness for 5th Quantile')
axs[1].set_title('Mean over  time of Pairwise directional Connectedness for 50th Quantile')

fig = plt.figure(figsize = (25,8))

fifth  =(net_5.abs()).sum(axis=1).groupby('date').sum()
fiftieth = (net_50.abs()).sum(axis=1).groupby('date').sum()
print stats.ttest_ind(fifth,fiftieth)

plt.plot(fifth.index,fifth, label = '5th Quantile Connection')
plt.plot(fiftieth.index,fiftieth, label = '50th Quantile Connection')

plt.xlabel("Quarter")
plt.ylabel("SUM OF PAIRWISE CONNECTEDNESS")
plt.legend()

Ttest_indResult(statistic=8.504477442026635, pvalue=5.34139944594878e-15)

CENTRALITY CALCULATION¶

CENTRALITY OF 5TH¶

In [94]:
centrality = []
for date in net_5.index.get_level_values(1):
    net_data = net_5.xs(date, level=1, drop_level=True)

    net = net_data.reset_index().melt(id_vars = ['country'],  var_name = 'source', value_name = 'weight')
    net = nx.from_pandas_edgelist(net, source =  'source', target = 'country', edge_attr = ['weight'], create_using = nx.DiGraph)

    centrality_t = nx.katz_centrality(net, weight = 'weight')
    centrality.append(centrality_t)
centrality = pd.DataFrame(centrality, index = net_5.index.get_level_values(1))

centrality.plot(figsize = (25,8))
plt.xlabel("Quarters")
plt.ylabel("Katz Centrality Score")
plt.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.005, 1), loc=2, borderaxespad=0)

<matplotlib.legend.Legend at 0x13592d310>
